    <text>
        <body>
            <div style="handwritten" type="letter">
                <head type="title">King Ferdinand I to Miklós Oláh (Innsbruck, 19 May 1552)</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p>He has received Oláh’s and István Dobó’s letter, from which he
                            understands how Dobó went about the matter of the Boldogkő castle. He is
                            sending back the letters Maximilian wrote in his absence: he has signed
                            them, Oláh should put the Hungarian seal on them, and they should be
                            sent out for enforcement so that he can recover the castle of Gyula. He
                            will take on the expenses Dobó incurred in this matter.</p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb/>
                <p>Ferdinandus etc. Reverendissime in Christo Pater, Fidelis sincere nobis
                    Dilecte!</p>
                <p>Redditae sunt nobis et tuae et egregii <persName>Stephani
                        Dobonis</persName><note type="critic">István Dobó.</note>
                    <del corresp="scriba">de P</del> arcis Agriensis castellani litterae,<note
                        type="critic">Oláh sent him Dobó’s letter, see Ep.
                        809.</note><ref>/o:olahus.tei.15520516_3</ref> ex quibus abunde intelleximus
                    tum ea, quae ipse <persName>Dobo</persName> iuxta mandatum et instructionem
                    nostram in negotio arcis <placeName>Baldokew</placeName><note type="critic"
                        >Castle of Boldogkő.</note> egit, tum etiam <del corresp="scriba"><gap
                            extent="1" reason="illegible" unit="word"/>
                    </del> praesertim autem ex litteris pro signatura ad nos missas ea, quae
                    serenissimo principi domino <persName>Maximiliano</persName> regi Bohemiae,
                    filio nostro carissimo atque tibi in eo ipso negotio a nobis scribi debere visa
                    sunt, probantes itaque clementer hanc dilectionis suae et tuam consultationem et
                    deliberationem, atque adeo litterarum desuper conscriptarum <del
                        corresp="scriba">cum</del> tenorem et continentiam illas manu nostra
                    significavimus, et tibi cum praesentibus remittimus, ut sigillo nostro Hungarico
                    per te <del corresp="scriba">obsignatae</del> primum obsignentur, et deinde ad
                    exsecutionem mittantur, ut restitutio arcis <placeName>Giwlae</placeName><note
                        type="critic">Gyula.</note> iam tandem fiat et ulterius id, quod plurimum
                    optamus, non differatur. <add corresp="scriba" type="insert">Expensas, quas ipse
                            <persName>Dobo</persName> iam faciet et adhuc facit in praesenti negotio
                        per Cameram nostram exsolvi ordinavimus.</add></p>
                <p>Datum <placeName>Oeniponti</placeName> die 19. Maii 1552.</p>
            </div>
            <div style="handwritten" type="verso">
                <head>Probably on the other side:</head>
                <p> Reverendissimo in Christo patri Nicolao Olaho episcopo Agriensi
                    compatri consiliario et in regno nostro Hungariae cancellario nostro, fideli et
                    sincero nobis dilecto.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
